{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Articulation Mapper\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This JSFX plugin allows you to define articulations which are triggered via Reaper's built-in notation features. This is similar to Expression Maps in Cubase or Articulation Sets in LogicPro.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 See the GitHub home page for full instructions:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 https://github.com/kbhaines/reaper/blob/main/articulation-mapper/README.md\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Features:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Articulations are triggered by notation attached to notes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Midi Notes and CC triggers, up to 4 per articulation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Simultaneous notes can have different articulations (no need to slightly separate the notes)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Up to 80 articulations per instance\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab UI displays currently triggered articulation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Default articulation can be set (when notes have no notation attached)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Default articulation can be changed by keyswitch (allows you to mix keyswitching & notation)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Simple text file based configuration (examples for Spitfire & VSL included)\sa180\par}
}
